---
import SiteNav from '../../components/SiteNav.astro';
import BaseHead from '../../components/BaseHead.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead title="Documentation â€“ contenteditable.lab" description="Documentation for contenteditable behavior and APIs." />
  </head>
  <body>
    <SiteNav />
    <main
      style="
        max-width: 1120px;
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 1.75rem 1.25rem 2.5rem;
      "
    >
      <header style="margin-bottom: 2rem;">
        <h1
          style="
            font-size: 2rem;
            line-height: 1.1;
            margin: 0 0 0.5rem 0;
          "
        >
          Documentation
        </h1>
        <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 0.95rem; color: var(--text-secondary);">
          Learn about the contenteditable attribute, its behavior, events, and browser compatibility.
        </p>
      </header>

      <div
        style="
          display: grid;
          grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
          gap: 1rem;
        "
      >
        <a href="/docs/what-is-contenteditable" class="doc-card">
          <h2
            style="
              font-size: 1.1rem;
              margin: 0 0 0.4rem 0;
            "
          >
            What is contenteditable?
          </h2>
          <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.5;">
            Introduction to the contenteditable attribute, its purpose, and basic usage.
          </p>
        </a>

        <a href="/docs/events" class="doc-card">
          <h2
            style="
              font-size: 1.1rem;
              margin: 0 0 0.4rem 0;
            "
          >
            Events
          </h2>
          <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.5;">
            Understanding input, beforeinput, composition, and other events in contenteditable.
          </p>
        </a>

        <a href="/docs/ime-composition" class="doc-card">
          <h2
            style="
              font-size: 1.1rem;
              margin: 0 0 0.4rem 0;
            "
          >
            IME & Composition
          </h2>
          <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.5;">
            How Input Method Editors work with contenteditable and composition events.
          </p>
        </a>

        <a href="/docs/selection-api" class="doc-card">
          <h2
            style="
              font-size: 1.1rem;
              margin: 0 0 0.4rem 0;
            "
          >
            Selection API
          </h2>
          <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.5;">
            Working with text selection, ranges, and the Selection API in contenteditable.
          </p>
        </a>

        <a href="/docs/execCommand-alternatives" class="doc-card">
          <h2
            style="
              font-size: 1.1rem;
              margin: 0 0 0.4rem 0;
            "
          >
            execCommand alternatives
          </h2>
          <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.5;">
            Modern alternatives to the deprecated execCommand API for formatting and editing.
          </p>
        </a>

        <a href="/docs/browser-compatibility" class="doc-card">
          <h2
            style="
              font-size: 1.1rem;
              margin: 0 0 0.4rem 0;
            "
          >
            Browser compatibility
          </h2>
          <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--text-muted); line-height: 1.5;">
            Overview of contenteditable support and behavior differences across browsers.
          </p>
        </a>
      </div>
    </main>
  </body>
</html>

<style>
  .doc-card {
    display: block;
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
    border: 1px solid var(--border-light);
    background: var(--bg-surface);
    padding: 1.1rem 1.2rem;
    text-decoration: none;
    color: var(--text-primary);
    transition: border-color 0.15s, box-shadow 0.15s;
  }
  
  .doc-card:hover {
    border-color: var(--text-primary);
    box-shadow: var(--card-shadow);
  }
</style>
